# Cursor AI Rules

## Commit Messages

When generating commit messages:

- Use imperative mood ("Add feature" not "Added feature")
- Keep the first line under 72 characters
- Use everyday words (start, end, use — not commence, terminate, utilise)
- Be direct and specific about what changed
- No filler words (basically, actually, essentially)
- Active voice only

Examples of good commit messages:
- Add World 2 campaign levels with time limit modifier
- Fix tile alignment on mobile Safari
- Update README with share system documentation

Examples to avoid:
- Updated the code to add new features
- Various improvements and fixes
- Basically added some stuff
